# UI Improvements from Reference Website

After analyzing the original design reference (`https://mnm.miraiznlabs.com/suhail-sahal-saleem/atheef-abdul-rahman-mnwz1xob?v=4`), it is clear that while we successfully matched the color scheme, layout structure, and Framer Motion logic, there are several ultra-premium **aesthetic micro-details** we can bring over to drastically elevate our Kerala theme.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> Please review these proposed stylistic upgrades. If you approve, I will automatically execute them and refine the components.

## Proposed Changes

### Global Styling & Textures (index.css & Layout)
- **Paper/Noise Texture**: The original utilizes subtle visual noise over the blurred backgrounds. I will inject a grainy SVG noise texture into our `bg-[#F8F7F4]` backdrop to make it feel like real expensive wedding card paper.
- **Glassmorphism Tuning**: The original's `.glass-card` effect has stronger light transmission (`border-white/40`, `bg-white/30`, `backdrop-blur-xl`). We will update our CSS to match this exact frosted depth.

---

### HeroCover.jsx
- **Capsule Badging**: Instead of just text, the original explicitly boxes "EXCLUSIVE INVITATION FOR ATHEEF" into a beautifully styled pill badge at the very top. We will wrap the `guestName` in a delicate, elegant badge with thin borders.
- **Improved Typography Hierachy**: We will decrease the tracking on the names ("Anand & Meera") to make the Cormorant Garamond font feel more connected and calligraphic, copying the huge, tight presentation in the original.

